Package cz.ive.exception

Specialized exceptions used in the IVE application.

See:
          Description

Exception Summary
AtomicCommitException This exception is thrown by the CommonProcessTemplate methods that are used to simplify writing of atomicCommit methods.
BreakpointActivationFailedException Exception raised when the breakpoint's activation fails.
DelegationFailedException Exception indicating delegation of some process failed.
EmptyCalendarException Exception raised when the calendar is asked to do a step, but nothing is planned.
ExchangeWrongSourcesException Exception raised when wrong sources are exchanged in the process.
HookNotPlannedException Exception raised when trying to cancel unplanned hook.
NoObjectPlaceException Exception raised when no WayPoint to place object when expanding an area is found for the object's class id.
ObjectRegistrationFailedException Exception raised when IveObject with some id is passed to ObjectMap to registration, but other object with same id is already registred.
OntologyNotSupportedException Exception beeing raised when some ontology driven object does not understand to given ontology identifier.
ProcessNotRunningException Exception beeing raised when attempt to stop process which is not running.
SimulationRunningException Exception beeing raised when attempt to set scheduling state during the running simulation.
StopDelegationFailedException  
 

Package cz.ive.exception Description

Specialized exceptions used in the IVE application. All are derived form java.lang.Exception. Only these exceptions are raised by IVE classes.
